  "type": "power",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You attempt to interrupt a creature in the process of casting a power. If the creature is casting a power of 3rd level or lower, its power fails and has no effect. If it is casting a power of 4th level or higher, make an ability check using your powercasting ability. The DC equals 10 + the power's level. On a success, the creature's power fails and has no effect.</p><p><strong>Higher Levels.&nbsp;</strong>When you cast this power using a power slot of 4th level or higher, the interrupted power has no effect if its level is less than or equal to the level of the power slot you used.</p>",
